-- African International to Buy 76% Stake in Ibhubesi
-- B y   J a n a   M a r a i s
-- 2012-04-19T13:19:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-19/african-international-s-ibubhesi-plan-to-cost-2-5-billion-1-.html
(Corrects size of stake bought in headline and first
paragraph.)  African International Energy Plc (7AE) 
said it will pay $270 million for a 76 percent stake in the
Ibhubesi gas project off the west coast of South Africa.  The field will be developed with the Petroleum Oil and Gas
Corp. of South Africa, which owns 24 percent, Chief Executive
Officer Aldworth Mbalati told reporters in Johannesburg today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jana Marais in Johannesburg at 
